{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:59+0000", "md5": "DAE11E702008F4FF95A533ED446AEC59", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "FaSNet being trained on a scale-invariant source to distortion ratio (SDR) loss function, it optimizes a compromise between SIR and SAR, that is why both values obtained with FaSNet are rather good and balanced.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005772113800048828}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001035928726196289}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 9}, "context": "The DANSE algorithm is a distributed MWF which aims at estimating the speech component s k,1 of the reference microphone of every node k [15], [30], [31].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00026684999465942383}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001169443130493164}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 7, "offsetEnd": 12}, "context": "In the DANSE algorithm, no fusion center gathers all the signals of all nodes.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010578036308288574}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.364418029785156e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 11, "offsetEnd": 15}, "context": "The pseudo-code of our algorithm is reported in Algorithm 1.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.45796066522598267}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.06651866436004639}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.45796066522598267}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.5800885558128357}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9434283971786499}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 11, "offsetEnd": 17}, "context": "We compare FaSNet to three versions of the Tango algorithm. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.5703935027122498}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.748603820800781e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "The original FaSNet architecture is a two-stage filtering where temporal convolutional network (TCN) blocks predict beamforming filters applied on the input channels, based on pair-wise normalized cross-correlations between the input channels.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008530616760253906}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0014744400978088379}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "The modified FaSNet is trained in the random room configuration in the same conditions as the CRNN, with the same amount of data, the same signals and the same input SIRs.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.018701672554016113}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.349781036376953e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 24, "offsetEnd": 29}, "context": "In previous versions of DANSE, only the target estimation was sent [10], [27], [31], [54].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9869792461395264}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.172325134277344e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 29, "offsetEnd": 34}, "context": "In their original version of DANSE, Bertrand and Moonen assumed that all the nodes of the network share the same VAD. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.007468283176422119}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.56978988647461e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 31, "offsetEnd": 35}, "context": "A Python implementation of the code that enabled us to create these datasets is available at https://github.com/nfurnon/disco/tree/master/dataset_ ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.012633204460144043}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.5800885558128357}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9434283971786499}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.45796066522598267}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.5800885558128357}, "shared": {"value": true, "score": 0.9434283971786499}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 37, "offsetEnd": 42}, "context": "Similarly to the original version of DANSE, the compressed signal is used to compute the speech and noise covariance matrices, but we additionally use it to better predict the TF mask with the multi-node DNN.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.01836329698562622}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.29425048828125e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 49, "offsetEnd": 54}, "context": "We name \"Tango\" this two-step algorithm based on DANSE.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00033664703369140625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "toolbox", "normalizedForm": "toolbox", "offsetStart": 50, "offsetEnd": 57}, "context": "We create three spatial scenarios with the Python toolbox Pyroomacoustics [37]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004954338073730469}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036243796348571777}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004954338073730469}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036243796348571777}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 57, "offsetEnd": 62}, "context": "In a two-node scenario, we introduced a batch-version of DANSE where at each node, a convolutional recurrent neural network (CRNN) predicted a TF mask out of the reference channel of the node and the compressed signal sent by the other node.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0053348541259765625}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9646909236907959}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Pyroomacoustics", "normalizedForm": "Pyroomacoustics", "offsetStart": 58, "offsetEnd": 77}, "context": "We create three spatial scenarios with the Python toolbox Pyroomacoustics [37]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004954338073730469}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036243796348571777}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004954338073730469}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036243796348571777}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 69, "offsetEnd": 74}, "context": "The results are given in Figure 9 and compared to the oracle case of DANSE, where the signal statistics are computed with an oracle voice activity detector (VADOR).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 74, "offsetEnd": 79}, "context": "To avoid issues related to convergence, we split the iterative process of DANSE into two distinct steps.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.7254857420921326}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.09304559230804443}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 82, "offsetEnd": 88}, "context": "Lastly, Tango relies on a much simpler DNN with 0.518 million parameters, whereas FaSNet counts 1.871 million parameters, which makes the DNN in Tango easier to train and quicker at inference time.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004600584506988525}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.318092346191406e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 87, "offsetEnd": 92}, "context": "Bertrand and Moonen introduced a distributed adaptive node-specific signal estimation (DANSE) algorithm, where each node, instead of sending all its signals to a fusion center, sends only one signal, called compressed signal, to the other nodes, thus reducing the bandwidth cost in addition to cancelling the need of a fusion center [15].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00013899803161621094}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.46956127882003784}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 113, "offsetEnd": 118}, "context": "By analysing its performance under various configurations, including real world ones, we confirm that it matches DANSE performance in terms of source to interferences ratio (SIR) and source to artifacts ratio (SAR) even when DANSE is implemented using an oracle voice activity detector (VADOR).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8288367390632629}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 116, "offsetEnd": 127}, "context": "To further challenge the performance of our solution, we compare it with a multi-channel end-to-end solution called FaSNet [48] which we implemented with the Asteroid toolbox [49]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004775404930114746}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 128, "offsetEnd": 134}, "context": "At inference, the trained neural network is applied on all nodes, and the best output is retained to compare the performance of FaSNet with the performance of our proposed Tango algorithm. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.010386765003204346}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 136, "offsetEnd": 142}, "context": "A good trade-off for example has been found with the fullrank SDW-MWF using \u00b5 = 5 (third line in Table II) which performs comparably to FaSNet.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.22338593006134033}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid toolbox", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid toolbox", "offsetStart": 158, "offsetEnd": 178}, "context": "To further challenge the performance of our solution, we compare it with a multi-channel end-to-end solution called FaSNet [48] which we implemented with the Asteroid toolbox [49]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004775404930114746}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004775404930114746}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 170, "offsetEnd": 176}, "context": "But the Tango algorithm, based on a SDW-MWF, leaves the freedom to have more noise reduction or speech distortion, which can be decided at run time whereas the output of FaSNet is fixed once the DNN is trained.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0035004615783691406}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001462697982788086}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSNet", "normalizedForm": "FaSNet", "offsetStart": 175, "offsetEnd": 181}, "context": "FaSNet being trained on a scale-invariant source to distortion ratio (SDR) loss function, it optimizes a compromise between SIR and SAR, that is why both values obtained with FaSNet are rather good and balanced.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005772113800048828}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001035928726196289}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9705191850662231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.11063408851623535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DANSE", "normalizedForm": "DANSE", "offsetStart": 225, "offsetEnd": 230}, "context": "By analysing its performance under various configurations, including real world ones, we confirm that it matches DANSE performance in terms of source to interferences ratio (SIR) and source to artifacts ratio (SAR) even when DANSE is implemented using an oracle voice activity detector (VADOR).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8288367390632629}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997225403785706}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9978773593902588}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 6176, "id": "3ce9a1a97165aacad35c2b6c223f582384283e88", "metadata": {"id": "3ce9a1a97165aacad35c2b6c223f582384283e88"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/downloads/xml/hal-02985867.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-02985867.grobid.tei.xml"}